Polymorphism - Having more than one form.

- Ability of objects of different classes to respond to the same method call in different way.
- It allows to write reusable and flexible code.

Real world example - GOD

When you father calls you - you react differently.
When your siblings call you - you react differntly.
When your spouse calls you - You react differently.

Types in java -

Compile time -
 - Achieved by Method overloading and Operator overloading.
Run time -
 - Achieved by Overriding.

Examples -
Operator overloading - 5+3 works as addition while "5"+3 works as concatination.

